text: Clarence Everett Howard (September 7, 1859 - May 2, 1930), or C. E. Howard, was an American politician, who was the fifteenth Mayor of Orlando in 1902. He served after Mayor James B. Parramore died in office.http://politicalgraveyard.com/bio/howard.html#309.11.02 ==References== Category:Mayors of Orlando, Florida Category:1859 births Category:1930 deaths
